main event: A civilian woman observed two circular objects, the size of a pea, maneuvering erratically in the sky over Teaneck, New Jersey on April 11, 1966.
interesting points: The objects were initially white, then turned dull red in color.
The objects were observed descending in a gliding configuration, then suddenly stopped, turned off their lights, and reversed course.
The witness observed the objects for approximately 7 minutes.
The weather conditions were cold and clear, with light winds.
The reporting officer believed the objects were likely an aircraft.
sighted object: two circular objects, the size of a pea
